text: Nicol Julieth Camacho Ariza (Vélez, Santander, October 24, 1999) is a Colombian professional soccer player. She plays for the Atlético Bucaramanga women's team in the Colombian Women's Football League. ==Life== Camacho first became interested in soccer at the age of eleven. She had to play with boys as there were no teams for girls. Her talent was spotted by Óscar Flórez who was the coach for Club Real Sociedad. She joined the women's team for Atlético Bucaramanga when she was 17 years old. She played for the Colombia National Team in the 2018 South American U-20 Women's Championship in Ecuador to qualify for the World Cup in France 2018. ==References== Category:1999 births Category:Atlético Bucaramanga footballers Category:Colombian women's footballers Category:Living people Category:Women's association football midfielders
